lement elementor-element-3fb9b3c elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"3fb9b3c\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-cc88e83\" data-id=\"cc88e83\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8fa06ee elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8fa06ee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Primary Hyperparathyroidism<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-e0b1d37 elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"e0b1d37\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-759c045\" data-id=\"759c045\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-95b11a0 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"95b11a0\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Definition<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Hypersecretion of PTH from the Parathyroid Gland<\/li><li>Causes:<ul><li>Single Parathyroid Adenoma (80%)<\/li><li>Four-Gland Parathyroid Hyperplasia (10-15%)<\/li><li>2-3-Gland Parathyroid Adenomas (4%)<\/li><li>Parathyroid Adenocarcinoma (1%)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Presentation<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Most are Asymptomatic<\/li><li>Symptoms of Hypercalcemia:<ul><li>Nephrolithiasis<\/li><li>Osteoporosis<\/li><li>Abdominal Pain<\/li><li>Urinary Frequency<\/li><li>Fatigue &amp; Delirium<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><em>Osteitis Fibrosa Cystica<\/em><ul><li>Brown Tumors from Ca Resorption<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Diagnosis<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Diagnosis: <strong>Labs <\/strong>&amp; <strong>Urine Calcium<\/strong><ul><li>Labs:<ul><li>High Calcium<\/li><li>Low Phosphorus<\/li><li>High Chloride<\/li><li>Acidosis<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Urine: <strong>High Urine Calcium<\/strong><ul><li>Rules Out <em>Familial Hypercalcemic Hypocalciuria<\/em><\/li><li>Calcium-to-Creatinine Clearance Ratio &gt; 0.02<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Most Specific Indicator: High <strong>Cl\/Phos Ratio &gt; 33<\/strong><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Localization: <strong>US &amp; Sestamibi Scan<\/strong> (Technetium 99m)<ul><li>US May Also Find Concomitant Thyroid Pathology<\/li><li>4-D CT May Also Be Available at Some Centers<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Concerning Signs for Adenocarcinoma<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Symptomatic<\/li><li><strong>Palpable<\/strong> Parathyroid Tumor<\/li><li>Calcium <strong>&gt; 13 mg\/dL<\/strong><ul><li>Mortality is Generally from Hypercalcemia<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>US: Irregular &amp; Fixed to Adjacent Tissue<ul><li>No FNA Indicated (Risk for Seeding)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Intraoperatively: Adherent &amp; Invading Thyroid with No Clear Plane<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Surgery Indications<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><strong>Symptoms<\/strong> of Hypercalcemia<\/li><li>Serum Calcium &gt; <strong>1.0 mg\/dL Above<\/strong> Normal Upper Limit<\/li><li>Renal Involvement:<ul><li>GFR &lt; 60 mL\/min<\/li><li>Nephrolithiasis<\/li><li>24-Hour Urine Calcium &gt; 400 mg\/Day<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li><strong>Significant<\/strong> Bone Loss (T-Score &lt; &#8211; 2.5)<\/li><li>Age<strong> &lt; 50<\/strong><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Surgical Treatment<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Adenoma: <strong>Minimally Invasive (Focused) Parathyroidectomy<\/strong><\/li><li>Hyperplasia or <strong>MEN I\/IIa<\/strong>: Bilateral Neck Exploration<ul><li>1-3 Enlarged: Resect All Diseased Glands<\/li><li>4 Enlarged: Subtotal (3.5 Gland) Resection or Total Parathyroidectomy with Autoimplantation<ul><li>Preferred Method Debated<\/li><li>Subtotal (3.5 Gland) Risks Neck Reoperation<\/li><li>Total Risks Hypoparathyroidism<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Adenocarcinoma: <strong>Radical Parathyroidectomy<\/strong> (En Bloc Resection with Thyroid Lobectomy)<ul><li>No Need for Prophylactic Lymph Node Dissection \u2013 High Morbidity with Low Risk of Metastases<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-c813b45\" data-id=\"c813b45\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-cdf6c72 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"cdf6c72\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-13385 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Parathyroid-Adenoma-OR.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"425\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Parathyroid-Adenoma-OR.jpg 500w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Parathyroid-Adenoma-OR-300x255.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p><p>Parathyroid Adenoma (White Arrow) and Normal Parathyroid (Black Arrow)\u00a0<sup>1<\/sup><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-d778e68 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"d778e68\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-13387 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Parathyroid-Adenoma-US.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"379\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Parathyroid-Adenoma-US.jpg 500w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/Parathyroid-Adenoma-US-300x227.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p><p>Parathyroid Adenoma on US <sup>2<\/sup><\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b3e91fd elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"b3e91fd\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><i